---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
const lastUpdated = "July 13, 2026";
---

<Layout
  title="Terms & Conditions — PSUCheck"
  description="PSUCheck Terms and Conditions: acceptable use, disclaimer of warranties, limitation of liability, and affiliate disclosure for psucheck.com."
>
  <div class="legal-page">
    <div class="legal-hero">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="badge badge-safe" style="margin-bottom:1rem;">Legal</div>
        <h1>Terms &amp; Conditions</h1>
        <p class="legal-meta">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="legal-body">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="legal-content">

          <div class="legal-summary card-accent">
            <strong>Plain-English Summary:</strong> PSUCheck provides calculator tools for informational
            purposes only. Our calculations are estimates — always verify PSU requirements before purchasing.
            We are not liable for hardware damage resulting from reliance on our estimates. Use our tools
            as a starting point, not a final authority.
          </div>

          <h2>1. Acceptance of Terms</h2>
          <p>
            By accessing or using PSUCheck (<strong>psucheck.com</strong>), you agree to be bound by
            these Terms and Conditions. If you do not agree to these terms, please do not use this website.
          </p>

          <h2>2. Description of Service</h2>
          <p>
            PSUCheck provides free online tools including a PC power supply (PSU) calculator, PC build
            cost estimator, and educational guides about PC building. All tools are provided for
            informational and educational purposes only.
          </p>

          <h2>3. Disclaimer of Warranties</h2>
          <p>
            <strong>PSUCheck's calculations are estimates based on published hardware specifications
            and industry-standard methodologies.</strong> We make no warranty, express or implied, that:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>Our wattage recommendations will be accurate for every specific hardware configuration</li>
            <li>Pricing information is current or reflects actual market prices</li>
            <li>Component specifications listed are free from errors or omissions</li>
            <li>A PSU meeting our recommended wattage will be compatible with your specific system</li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            Power supply requirements vary based on factors including overclocking settings, ambient
            temperature, PSU age and quality, and specific component manufacturing variances. Our
            recommendations are starting points — you should verify requirements with your specific
            hardware documentation and consult professional resources when building high-value systems.
          </p>

          <h2>4. Limitation of Liability</h2>
          <p>
            To the maximum extent permitted by applicable law, PSUCheck and its operators shall not
            be liable for any indirect, incidental, special, consequential, or punitive damages,
            including but not limited to:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>Hardware damage resulting from an undersized or incompatible power supply</li>
            <li>Financial losses from purchasing components based on our cost estimates</li>
            <li>Data loss or system instability resulting from power-related events</li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            Your use of PSUCheck's calculator tools is entirely at your own risk.
          </p>

          <h2>5. Affiliate Relationships</h2>
          <p>
            PSUCheck participates in affiliate programs including <strong>Amazon Associates</strong>
            and the <strong>Newegg Affiliate Program</strong>. Product links on this site may be affiliate
            links. When you make a purchase through these links, PSUCheck may receive a commission.
          </p>
          <p>
            Affiliate relationships do not influence our calculator results or product recommendations.
            We recommend products based on technical specifications and value — not commission rates.
          </p>

          <h2>6. Intellectual Property</h2>
          <p>
            The PSUCheck name, logo, design, and original written content are the intellectual property
            of PSUCheck. Hardware specifications, TDP figures, and pricing data are sourced from
            publicly available manufacturer and third-party databases and are not claimed as our own.
          </p>
          <p>
            You may not reproduce, republish, or redistribute PSUCheck's original content without
            written permission. Linking to our pages is encouraged.
          </p>

          <h2>7. Third-Party Services</h2>
          <p>PSUCheck uses the following third-party services:</p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Plausible Analytics</strong> — privacy-preserving traffic analytics</li>
            <li><strong>Google AdSense</strong> — advertising services</li>
            <li><strong>Formspree</strong> — contact form processing</li>
            <li><strong>Cloudflare Pages</strong> — website hosting and CDN</li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            Each service is subject to its own terms of service and privacy policy. PSUCheck is not
            responsible for the practices of these third-party services.
          </p>

          <h2>8. Acceptable Use</h2>
          <p>You agree not to:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Use PSUCheck's tools for any unlawful purpose</li>
            <li>Attempt to scrape, copy, or reproduce our database content at scale without permission</li>
            <li>Use automated tools to generate excessive traffic to our servers</li>
            <li>Impersonate PSUCheck or claim affiliation with us</li>
          </ul>

          <h2>9. Changes to Terms</h2>
          <p>
            We reserve the right to modify these Terms at any time. The "Last updated" date at the top
            of this page reflects the most recent revision. Continued use of PSUCheck after changes
            constitutes acceptance of the updated terms.
          </p>

          <h2>10. Governing Law</h2>
          <p>
            These Terms shall be governed by applicable law. Any disputes arising from use of PSUCheck
            shall be resolved through good-faith negotiation before any formal proceedings.
          </p>

          <h2>11. Contact</h2>
          <p>
            For questions about these Terms, please use our <a href="/contact">Contact page</a>.
          </p>

        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>

<style>
.legal-hero {
  padding: 4rem 0 2rem;
  background: linear-gradient(180deg, var(--bg-deep) 0%, var(--bg-primary) 100%);
  border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-subtle);
}
.legal-meta {
  color: var(--text-tertiary);
  font-size: 0.875rem;
  margin-top: 0.5rem;
}
.legal-body {
  padding: 3rem 0 5rem;
}
.legal-content {
  max-width: 760px;
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  gap: 1.5rem;
}
.legal-content h2 {
  font-size: 1.375rem;
  padding-bottom: 0.5rem;
  border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-subtle);
}
.legal-content p {
  color: var(--text-secondary);
  line-height: 1.75;
  max-width: 70ch;
}
.legal-content ul {
  padding-left: 1.5rem;
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  gap: 0.4rem;
  color: var(--text-secondary);
  line-height: 1.6;
}
.legal-summary {
  font-size: 0.9375rem;
  line-height: 1.6;
  color: var(--text-secondary);
}
</style>
